t135.text: Once we have shown that goats managed this way can work to improve our hills we'll be in a position to sell surplus breeding goats and trained LGDs to others that want to do it. The current price on goat is close to $10/kg so it should be worth it.

t136.text: We found the goat behavior of parking their kids made them vulnerable to fox and eagle attack. We can't shoot all the foxes or any of the eagles so the LGDs are an experiment that should pay dividends soon.

t137.text: I'm reading a bit online. I'm only of only a few Boer goat farmers this side of Adelaide and have a small herd of 150 breeders heading for 300+. We're rotationally grazing goats through scrub paddocks. Aiming to improve soils and grass populations. Not many are doing this in SA.

t138.text: There are not too many farmers using LGDs on commercial farms in SA. It's very new to us, I aim to have them out with the main goat mob for the first time this week.
